OL,3,CParts of UK may get 'brief respite'
OL,4,Cfrom scorching weather
OL,6,FOn Sunday, two men died after entering
OL,7,Fthe water to help two children who had
OL,8,Fcome into difficulty at Seaton Carew
OL,9,Fbeach in Hartlepool.
OL,11,FSuperintendent Glen Ward, of Cleveland
OL,12,FPolice, said: "We know it is inviting
OL,13,Fin the hot weather, but we would
OL,14,Fencourage people to refrain from
OL,15,Fentering any open water at all. Today
OL,16,Fwe have sadly seen the true tragedy
OL,17,Fthat can happen as a result."
OL,19,FIt followed a number of water-related
OL,20,Fdeaths in recent days amid the
OL,21,Fscorching weather.
OL,26,@tD@OOUyD@]O]
